# TESTING PROTOCOL

## Testing Cadence — When Ryan Should Test

**NEVER prompt testing after:**
- Content-only sessions (JSON files, audio scripts, markdown, documentation)
- Prompt writing or Claude Pro sprint prep
- Rule or protocol updates

**ALWAYS prompt testing after:**
- Any code session that touches QuestGrid, useMasteryStore, useUserStore, or `app/_layout.tsx`
- Any Skia component change (StarlightSpirit, StickerCanvas)
- Any navigation, routing, or animation change
- Any new screen or new route added
- Any AsyncStorage or Supabase change

**Device guidance — Two-Tier System:**

Tier 1 — Ryan's iPhone 17 Pro Max (solo, fast):
- Run after every major code session before coordinating with Amber
- Catches crashes, broken navigation, obvious UI issues, audio problems
- Does NOT catch: RAM limits, Skia/Android rendering bugs, Fire OS gesture differences
- Goal: "Does it work at all?" — 5 minutes, catches obvious problems

Tier 2 — Fire HD 10 with Amber and Libby in Tennessee (coordinated, milestone only):
- Only schedule after Tier 1 passes cleanly
- Required for: Skia rendering, gesture handling, performance at 3GB RAM, child UX observation
- Coordinate session timing with Amber in advance — do not waste her or Libby's time debugging
- When approaching a milestone test, flag Ryan to plan the Amber session at least a few days ahead
- Details on remote coordination (video call, screen share, recording) to be planned when Phase 1 is ready

Fire HD 10 is REQUIRED (Tier 2) before declaring any phase complete or before Libby uses the app independently.

**Four milestone tests — surface these proactively at phase completion:**

| Milestone | Focus |
|---|---|
| Phase 1 complete | Quest grid shows real stickers from JSON. Mastery tracking works. Session lock triggers. |
| Phase 2 complete | Audio plays. Sticker art loads. Story screens render without crashing. |
| Phase 3 complete | Motion verify works. Camera data stays on device. No transmission. |
| Pre-Libby | Full 15-minute session as Libby. Run child safety checklist. Parent PIN tested. |

